{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Add LangGraph Hybrid System",
  "description": "Add LangGraph for dynamic query routing and tool integration",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Create a LangGraph-based hybrid RAG system with the following:\n\n1. Create LangGraph orchestration node that routes queries to:\n   - RAG (for static document knowledge)\n   - Knowledge Graph (for structured entity relationships)\n   - Tools (for dynamic data like web scraping, API calls)\n\n2. Add web scraping capability using BeautifulSoup to fetch web data\n\n3. Add dynamic tool integration for real-time data\n\n4. Create evaluation framework to assess response quality\n\nThe system should use the existing RAG pipeline, Knowledge Graph manager, and Groq LLM client.\n\nCreate these files:\n- rag/langgraph_orchestrator.py - LangGraph workflow\n- rag/web_scraper.py - Web scraping with BeautifulSoup\n- rag/tools.py - Dynamic tools/API integration\n- rag/evaluation.py - Evaluation framework\n\nMake sure to:\n- Use the existing Groq LLM client for consistency\n- Integrate with existing Neo4j knowledge graph\n- Use MongoDB for storing chat history\n- Include proper error handling and logging"
  }
}